# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# governance-core self-hosting (P-0066): the autonomy layer.
#
# These root-level directories are INSTALL ARTIFACTS — pure derivatives that
# `governance-core install` regenerates from the package source. They are NOT
# committed (single repo, single agent: nothing to propagate to other clones).
# Run `governance-core install --project-root .` after a fresh clone.
#
# Leading-slash anchored: these patterns must match ONLY the repo root, never
# the package source under governance_core/ (e.g. governance_core/tools/ stays
# committed — it is the SOURCE; root /tools/ is the self-installed copy).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
/.claude/hooks/
/.claude/skills/
/.claude/commands/
/.claude/agents/
/contracts/
/agent_rules/
/tools/
/knowledge/
/.governance/clauses/

# Runtime state — in-flight proposals etc. (constitution Art.4.1: never in git;
# terminal proposals are archived to /proposals/_archive/ which IS committed).
/shared_state/
